    "source_sections": {
      "references": "[ErGr80] Erd\\H{o}s, P. and Graham, R., Old and new problems and results in combinatorial number theory. Monographies de L'Enseignement Mathematique (1980).\n \n [Gr64d] Graham, R. L., A property of Fibonacci numbers. Fibonacci Quart. (1964), 1-10.",
      "remarks": "Graham \\cite{Gr64d} has shown that the sequence $a_n=F_n-(-1)^{n}$, where $F_n$ is the $n$th Fibonacci number, has these properties. Erd\\H{o}s and Graham \\cite{ErGr80} remark that it is easy to see that if $a_{n+1}/a_n>\\frac{1+\\sqrt{5}}{2}$ then the second property is automatically satisfied, and that it is not hard to construct very irregular sequences satisfying both properties."
    },
